  "text": "The algorithm divides the covered area into a regular two-dimensional grid. For each grid cell, the minimum z-value of all points, which fall into this cell, is stored. The result is a simplified terrain model. This approach is originally based on the paper by [CITATION_1] . It was refined by adding additional diagonal scan lines.",
